{"title": "Daniel Boone, Backwoodsman", "description": "Daniel Boone is celebrated in history and legend as one of the foremost pioneers who opened up the wilderness of Kentucky.  Famed for his skills as a hunter, he was once captured and adopted by the Shawnee tribe from which he ultimately escaped.  He was active in the militia and fought in several battles of the American Revolution.  In later life he became a politician, being elected to Virginia state assembly, and land speculator, eventually settling in Missouri.<br><br>\r\n\r\nThis biography is written for youth in a lively and engaging style dramatizing many of the events of Boone\u2019s adventures, from his youth to his final days.\r\n - Summary by Larry Wilson", "duration": 24477, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "16385", "name": "C. H. Forbes-Lindsay"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/daniel_boone_backwoodsman_2112_librivox/danielboone_2112.jpg", "copyright_year": "1909", "genres": ["Biography"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Larry Wilson"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Mozartjr"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The American Backwoodsman", "readers": [8638], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/daniel_boone_backwoodsman_2112_librivox/danielboone_01_forbeslindsay_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1069}, {"section": 2, "title": "Hardy Goodfellow", "readers": [16713], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/daniel_boone_backwoodsman_2112_librivox/danielboone_02_forbeslindsay_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1151}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Young Hunter", "readers": [11585], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/daniel_boone_backwoodsman_2112_librivox/danielboone_03_forbeslindsay_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1195}, {"section": 4, "title": "The Daring Pioneer", "readers": [11585], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/daniel_boone_backwoodsman_2112_librivox/danie